  "title": "Airfreight Account Support Executive (East) [EL]",
  "description": "<h3><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Act as the main point of contact for customers on airfreight shipments and inquiries.</p></li><li><p>Handle booking requests, shipment status updates, and service-related issues.</p></li><li><p>Coordinate closely with internal operations, airlines, and overseas agents to ensure smooth shipment execution.</p></li><li><p>Prepare and verify airfreight documentation such as Air Waybills (AWB), invoices, and packing lists.</p></li><li><p>Monitor shipment schedules and proactively update customers on delays or changes.</p></li><li><p>Resolve customer complaints professionally and follow up to ensure satisfaction.</p></li><li><p>Maintain accurate records in the system and support billing-related queries.</p></li><li><p>Build and maintain strong customer relationships to support long-term partnerships.</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Requirements</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Diploma or Degree in Logistics, Supply Chain, or related field.</p></li><li><p>Minimum 1–3 years of experience in airfreight customer service or freight forwarding.</p></li><li><p>Familiar with airfreight documentation, Incoterms, and airline procedures.</p></li><li><p>Strong communication and coordination skills.</p></li><li><p>Detail-oriented, customer-focused, and able to work under pressure.</p></li></ul><p><br />We regret only shortlisted candidates will be contacted. All applications will be handled confidentially. By submitting your application, you agree to the collection, use, retention, and disclosure of your personal information to prospective employers.</p><p>Wecruit Pte Ltd</p><p>EA License No: 20C0270</p>",
